"{\"Course Name\": \"CAPITALISM AND ITS DISCONTENTS\", \"Course Level\": \"2913\", \"Dept Abbreviation\": \"HI\", \"Course Description\": \"Cat. II This course focuses on modern capitalism as an economic, social, and cultural formation in global perspective. As capitalism has radically changed the way humans live and work, critics have articulated their various discontents. Topics to be discussed include colonialism, enslavement, industrialization, social movements, automation, climate change, and global inequality. In addition to our readings, students will directly engage with the rich materials on global labor history available at WPI and in Worcester. This course will be offered in 2021-22, and in alternating years thereafter.\\r\\n\", \"Requirements\": [], \"Is Cat 1\": false, \"Start Year For Cat 2\": \"2021\"}"